news.title: Prism Johnson' net loss narrows to ₹5.56 in Q1 FY26
news.para: Prism Johnson reported a consolidated net loss after tax of ₹5.56 crore for the quarter ended June 30, 2025, a notable improvement from the ₹18.26 crore loss in the same period last year. The company's total income grew by 9.60% to ₹1,929.92 crore.

news.title: Crompton Greaves Consumer Electricals' net profit declines 18.67% in Q1 FY26
news.para: Crompton Greaves Consumer Electricals experienced an 18.67% decline in net consolidated profit, reaching ₹123.90 crore in Q1 FY26. Net consolidated total income also dipped by 6.45% to ₹2,022.05 crore. Despite this, the lighting segment showed resilience with stable revenue and a 41% surge in EBIT, resulting in margin expansion.

news.title: Vacant land tax committee to recover over ₹870 crore tax dues in Vijayawada
news.para: NTR district administration formed a Vacant Land Tax Committee. The aim is to recover pending vacant land taxes within Vijayawada Municipal Corporation limits. The committee includes revenue officials from both VMC and NTR district. They will work with town planning and registration departments. The goal is to address the low tax collection rate.

news.title: BNW Developments targets ₹20,000 crore worth of projects by next year
news.para: UAE-based BNW Developments, spearheaded by Ankur Aggarwal and Vivek Anand Oberoi, is set to launch projects worth Rs 20,000 crore next year, building on their existing Rs 10,000 crore portfolio.

news.title: ITC Hotels to develop Fortune Select hotel in Lucknow
news.para: ITC Hotels is expanding its Fortune Hotels portfolio with a new agreement with CEM Hospitality for a hotel in Lucknow, slated to open in 2026. This addition strengthens ITC's presence in Uttar Pradesh to seven operational properties, with six more in development. The new hotel will feature 93 modern rooms and diverse dining options.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body's road projects to affect 8,767 properties
news.para: Ahmedabad Municipal Corporation (AMC) plans to widen and open over 200 roads. This will affect 8,767 properties across the city. Work will begin soon on 103 roads in five zones. Alternative arrangements will be made for residents with proof of residence before 2010. Compensation will be provided for legally acquired properties.

news.title: NBCC India's net profit rises 25.97% in Q1 FY26
news.para: NBCC (India) announced a significant surge in its financial performance for the first quarter of fiscal year 2026, showcasing a 25.97% increase in net consolidated profit, reaching ₹135.03 crore. The company's total income also experienced substantial growth, rising by 12.26% to ₹2,465.48 crore.

news.title: Country Garden's liquidation hearing adjourned to January 5
news.para: Country Garden, the Chinese property developer, has secured an adjournment of a Hong Kong High Court liquidation hearing until January 5, 2026. The company defaulted on its offshore debt in late 2023 and is seeking creditor support for a restructuring proposal to reduce $14.1 billion of debt by 78%. This support is crucial to fend off the liquidation petition.

news.title: JSW Cement to triple capacity to 60 million tonnes a year
news.para: JSW Cement's Rs 3,600-crore IPO is now open, with plans to triple manufacturing capacity to 60 million tonnes per annum. The company may tap capital markets for funding, considering QIP or follow-on offerings. JSW Cement expects industry growth of 6-7% this fiscal year, focusing on reducing logistics costs and evaluating acquisition opportunities.

news.title: JSW Cement IPO subscribed 29% on day 1 of offer
news.para: JSW Cement's IPO witnessed 29% subscription on its first day, with strong interest from retail investors and qualified institutional buyers. The IPO includes a fresh issue and an offer-for-sale by existing shareholders like Apollo Management and SBI. Proceeds will fund a new cement unit in Rajasthan and debt repayment, valuing the company at ₹20,000 crore.

news.title: Meghalaya cabinet approves reforms in building by-laws
news.para: "Under the new bylaws, all applications for building permits must be submitted online," Chief Minister Conrad K Sangma, who chaired the meeting, said.

news.title: IFC commits $150 million to HDFC Capital's H-DREAM fund
news.para: IFC is investing $150 million in H-DREAM Fund, managed by HDFC Capital Advisors, to boost sustainable, affordable housing across urban India. The $1 billion fund aims to construct 25,000 green-certified units, addressing the nation's housing shortage. This initiative seeks to mobilize $850 million from investors, supporting early-stage financing and green building standards.

news.title: Government to introduce new bill to enhance CE industry's competitiveness: Road transport minister
news.para: Nitin Gadkari highlighted the financial and environmental benefits of green fuels and advanced technologies for the construction equipment industry at the ICEMA Annual Session 2025. He emphasized sustainability, quality, and innovation to meet rising global demand. The industry saw 3% growth in FY25, with increased equipment sales and exports, and the government plans policy support to address industry challenges.

news.title: JCB India revises growth target for FY26 amid industry challenges
news.para: Deepak Shetty, CEO and MD of JCB India said that the first half of the financial year has been challenging due to a slowdown in infrastructure development and the introduction of new stage 5 emission norms in January, which created market uncertainty and impacted sales.

news.title: Signature Global India posts net profit of ₹34.43 crore in Q1 FY26
news.para: Signatureglobal (India) announced a significant surge in its financial performance for Q1 FY26, reporting a net consolidated profit after tax of ₹34.43 crore, a substantial increase from ₹6.79 crore in the same quarter last year. The company's total income also saw impressive growth, reaching ₹898.35 crore, driven by strong pre-sales and improved sales realization.

news.title: Maharashtra government sanctions funds to acquire rovers for land survey
news.para: The Maharashtra government has sanctioned Rs 1,732 crore to modernize land survey operations and improve revenue department infrastructure. A significant portion, Rs 132 crore, will fund 1,200 advanced rovers for faster land measurement under the e-Survey 2.0 project.

news.title: Gurugram & Manesar civic bodies now take AI route to boost property tax collection
news.para: Gurugram and Manesar municipal corporations are leveraging artificial intelligence to significantly boost property tax revenue. MCG has already collected Rs 200 crore, 72% of its FY26 target, while MCM surpassed its previous fiscal year's collection. AI identifies defaulters, addresses their concerns through a bot, and facilitates payments, leading to increased revenue generation.

news.title: Goa brings bill to reduce stamp duty in some cases
news.para: Goa's government introduced a bill to lower stamp duty on property mortgages without possession transfer and encourage trust deed registration for family benefits. The bill, named The Indian Stamp (Goa Amendment) Bill, 2025, aims to rationalize stamp duty on mortgage and trust instruments.

news.title: Unique number, QR code to aid house tracing, emergency services in Bhubaneswar
news.para: The Bhubaneswar Municipal Corporation has initiated the installation of permanent digital door number (DDN) plates across the city to simplify house searches and improve emergency service response. Each plate features a unique number and QR code, which will be integrated into a BMC app for easy location access.

news.title: Telangana HC orders inquiry into alleged illegal constructions at Nandagiri Hills
news.para: The Telangana High Court has ordered a probe into alleged illegal construction by Net Net Ventures at Nandagiri Hills. Justice K Lakshman directed a detailed inquiry following a petition by a cooperative society. The inquiry will examine a Vigilance & Enforcement report highlighting deviations. It will also look into the role of former GHMC Commissioner Amrapali Kata.
